Package camzup.core

Class CurveEntity2

java.lang.Object
camzup.core.Entity
camzup.core.Entity2
camzup.core.CurveEntity2
All Implemented Interfaces:
IEntity, IOriented2, ISpatial2, ISvgWritable, IUtils, IVolume, IVolume2, java.lang.Iterable<Curve2>
public class CurveEntity2
extends Entity2
implements java.lang.Iterable<Curve2>, IVolume2, ISvgWritable
An entity which contains a transform that is applied to a list of curves.

      public java.lang.String toSvgElm​(java.lang.String id, float zoom)

    • toSvgElm

      public java.lang.String toSvgElm​(java.lang.String id, float zoom, MaterialSolid[] materials)
      Creates a string representing a group node in the SVG format. This SVG is designed for compatibility with Processing, not for efficiency.

      Stroke weight is impacted by scaling in transforms, so zoom is a parameter. If nonuniform zooming is used, zoom can be an average of width and height or the maximum dimension.
      Parameters:
      id - the curve id prefix
      zoom - scaling from external transforms
      materials - the array of materials
      Returns:
      the string
